# Project Design Consistency Rules

When generating or modifying UI code for this project, always reference the existing design patterns implemented in:

- Home page "About" section
- Home page "Statistics" section
- /partners page

These sections represent the current visual design system of the website.

## Design Consistency Requirements

When creating or updating components or pages:

1. Match the layout patterns used in the reference sections
2. Reuse existing component structures where possible
3. Follow the same spacing scale and section padding
4. Maintain consistent typography hierarchy (headings, subheadings, body)
5. Use the same card styles, grid systems, and alignment patterns
6. Follow the same button styles and interaction patterns
7. Maintain consistent responsive behavior

## Implementation Guidance

- Prefer reusing existing components instead of creating new ones
- If a similar pattern exists in the reference sections, adapt it rather than inventing a new layout
- Keep styling consistent with the existing Tailwind/CSS patterns already used
- Avoid introducing new design systems, spacing rules, or typography styles

## Goal

All new sections and pages should visually feel like they belong to the same design system established by the About section, Statistics section, and Partners page.